---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="FraiseQL vs Alternatives - Honest Comparisons"
  description="Compare FraiseQL to Hasura, PostGraphile, Apollo Server, and Prisma. When to choose which tool."
>
  <div style="padding: 2rem; max-width: 1280px; margin: 0 auto;">
    <h1>FraiseQL vs Alternatives</h1>
    <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; color: #666;">
      Honest comparisons to help you choose the right tool for your use case.
    </p>

    <section style="margin: 3rem 0;">
      <h2>Quick Comparison Matrix</h2>
      <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1rem 0;">
        <thead>
          <tr style="background: #f5f3ff;">
            <th style="padding: 1rem; text-align: left; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">Feature</th>
            <th style="padding: 1rem; text-align: center; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">FraiseQL</th>
            <th style="padding: 1rem; text-align: center; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">Hasura</th>
            <th style="padding: 1rem; text-align: center; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">PostGraphile</th>
            <th style="padding: 1rem; text-align: center; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">Prisma</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td style="padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;"><strong>Compilation</strong></td>
            <td style="padding: 1rem; text-align: center; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">Build-time ✓</td>
            <td style="padding: 1rem; text-align: center; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">Runtime</td>
            <td style="padding: 1rem; text-align: center; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">Runtime</td>
            <td style="padding: 1rem; text-align: center; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">Generate-time</td>
          </tr>
          <tr style="background: #fafafa;">
            <td style="padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;"><strong>Multi-Database</strong></td>
            <td style="padding: 1rem; text-align: center; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">4 ✓</td>
            <td style="padding: 1rem; text-align: center; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">PostgreSQL only</td>
            <td style="padding: 1rem; text-align: center; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">PostgreSQL only</td>
            <td style="padding: 1rem; text-align: center; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">4</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td style="padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;"><strong>N+1 Prevention</strong></td>
            <td style="padding: 1rem; text-align: center; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">Guaranteed ✓</td>
            <td style="padding: 1rem; text-align: center; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">Runtime detection</td>
            <td style="padding: 1rem; text-align: center; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">Runtime detection</td>
            <td style="padding: 1rem; text-align: center; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">Developer responsible</td>
          </tr>
          <tr style="background: #fafafa;">
            <td style="padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;"><strong>Auditability</strong></td>
            <td style="padding: 1rem; text-align: center; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">100% ✓</td>
            <td style="padding: 1rem; text-align: center; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">Partial</td>
            <td style="padding: 1rem; text-align: center; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">Partial</td>
            <td style="padding: 1rem; text-align: center; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">Partial</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td style="padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;"><strong>Ecosystem</strong></td>
            <td style="padding: 1rem; text-align: center; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">11 tools ✓</td>
            <td style="padding: 1rem; text-align: center; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">Plugins</td>
            <td style="padding: 1rem; text-align: center; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">Plugins</td>
            <td style="padding: 1rem; text-align: center; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">Single tool</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 3rem 0;">
      <h2>Detailed Comparisons</h2>

      <div style="margin: 2rem 0; padding: 1rem; border-left: 4px solid #e63946; background: #fafafa;">
        <h3><a href="/vs/hasura" style="color: #e63946; text-decoration: none;">vs Hasura →</a></h3>
        <p><strong>Approach:</strong> Hasura introspects DB at runtime; FraiseQL compiles at build time.</p>
        <p><strong>When to choose Hasura:</strong> Need rapid schema changes, small teams, prototyping</p>
        <p><strong>When to choose FraiseQL:</strong> Need predictable performance, auditability, production compliance</p>
      </div>

      <div style="margin: 2rem 0; padding: 1rem; border-left: 4px solid #059669; background: #fafafa;">
        <h3><a href="/vs/postgraphile" style="color: #059669; text-decoration: none;">vs PostGraphile →</a></h3>
        <p><strong>Approach:</strong> PostGraphile is PostgreSQL-only; FraiseQL supports 4 databases.</p>
        <p><strong>When to choose PostGraphile:</strong> PostgreSQL-only stack, prefer plugins</p>
        <p><strong>When to choose FraiseQL:</strong> Multi-database support, ecosystem approach, higher performance</p>
      </div>

      <div style="margin: 2rem 0; padding: 1rem; border-left: 4px solid #2563eb; background: #fafafa;">
        <h3><a href="/vs/apollo" style="color: #2563eb; text-decoration: none;">vs Apollo Federation →</a></h3>
        <p><strong>Approach:</strong> Apollo federates multiple services; FraiseQL is single-schema compiled.</p>
        <p><strong>When to choose Apollo:</strong> Multiple independent teams, federated schema</p>
        <p><strong>When to choose FraiseQL:</strong> Monolithic API, deterministic queries, strong consistency</p>
      </div>

      <div style="margin: 2rem 0; padding: 1rem; border-left: 4px solid #dc2626; background: #fafafa;">
        <h3><a href="/vs/prisma" style="color: #dc2626; text-decoration: none;">vs Prisma →</a></h3>
        <p><strong>Approach:</strong> Prisma is ORM with generated clients; FraiseQL generates SQL directly.</p>
        <p><strong>When to choose Prisma:</strong> Developer ergonomics priority, rapid prototyping</p>
        <p><strong>When to choose FraiseQL:</strong> Performance priority, database-first architecture, analytics workloads</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 3rem 0;">
      <h2>The FraiseQL Philosophy</h2>
      <p>
        FraiseQL is not the right choice for every project. We're optimized for:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>✅ Production APIs with strong consistency requirements</li>
        <li>✅ Regulated industries (HIPAA, PCI-DSS, SOC 2)</li>
        <li>✅ Analytics and reporting workloads</li>
        <li>✅ Multi-database deployments</li>
        <li>✅ Performance-critical systems</li>
        <li>❌ NOT ideal for: Rapid prototyping, small hobby projects, learning GraphQL</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <p style="margin-top: 3rem;">
      <a href="/">← Back to Home</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
